 England, United Kingdom":"Devizes, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom","Swinton by New Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Swinton by New Malton, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Tison","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: nickname from Old French <i>tison</i> ‘piece of wood’ and ‘firebrand’, in the latter sense perhaps denoting someone with a fiery temperament.","French (Nord and Pas-de-Calais): ethnic name from a derivative of Old French <i>teis</i> ‘German, Flemish’, from ancient Germanic <i>theod</i> ‘people’. Compare   Teson   and   Tesson  .","Possibly also an Americanized form of German   Theissen   or   Theisen  . Compare   Tyson  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Tesson","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Arnaud, Elmire, Gaston, Pierre.","French (mainly Vendée and Normandy): from <i>tesson</i>, a dialect word meaning ‘badger’, applied as a nickname for someone thought to resemble the animal in some way.","Altered form of French   Tison  . Compare   Teson  ."]},{"name":"Teson","meanings":["Altered form of French   Tison  . Compare   Tesson  ."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Hebrew: The Scripture name, in Hebrew, Adham, signifying 'man;' literally earthy, red earth; Rudolph, however, says the name in Ethiopic means ' to be fair, beautiful.' Hence the nurse-name Addy, little Adam."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adam Tison was born about 1095, in Devizes, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of Gilbert Tison and Unknown. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Emma. He died about 1159, in Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 66."},"et":{"about 1095–about 1159":"umbes 1095–umbes 1159","1095–1159":"1095–1159","1085–1154":"1085–1154","1110–1191":"1110–1191","1115–1180":"1115–1180","–Male":"Surnud","1060–1124":"1060–1124","–Female":"Surnud","1115-1120":"1115 kuni 1120","about 1095":"